To provide comprehensive information about studying at Charles University Faculty of Medicine in Hradec Kralove, let's address some frequently asked questions (FAQs) that prospective students often have:
What are the entry requirements for studying medicine at Charles University Faculty of Medicine in Hradec Kralove?
Applicants must have completed secondary education equivalent to the Czech Maturita exam.
Proficiency in English or Czech language is required. For non-native English speakers, language proficiency tests such as TOEFL or IELTS may be necessary.
Applicants may need to pass an entrance examination in biology and chemistry.
Is the medical program at Charles University Faculty of Medicine accredited?
Yes, the medical programs offered by Charles University Faculty of Medicine are accredited by the Czech Ministry of Education, Youth, and Sports.
What is the duration of the medical program at Charles University Faculty of Medicine?
The General Medicine (MD) program typically spans six years, including pre-clinical and clinical phases.
Other programs such as Dentistry and Pharmacy have their own duration requirements.
Can international students study medicine in Hradec Kralove?
Yes, Charles University Faculty of Medicine welcomes international students to its programs.
International students are required to meet the same academic and language proficiency requirements as Czech students.
